Preheat the #oven{} to 200°C. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}, discard the core and the seeds then chop into small pieces. Zest and chop the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Add the pepper and @Mexican style spice mix{1} to the beef mince and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Mix in the @Worcester sauce{15%ml}, @tomato passata{1}, kidney beans and @beef stock paste{10%g}. Using the back of a #spoon{}, crush half the beans once they're in the pan. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat to low-medium and simmer until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} in a single layer on a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and drizzle over some more oil. Bake in the oven until crispy and golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Mix the lime zest into the @soured cream{75%g}.

Serve the crisp tacos on plates. Top with a generous helping of the Mexican-spiced beef mince. Spoon on a dollop of zesty soured cream and a sprinkling of the spring onion. Serve with lime wedges alongside. Enjoy!